              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>-\frac{\sqrt{6}}{4}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{\sqrt{2}}{4}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{\sqrt{2}}{4}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>0</li>
            </ol>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
  
    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Real-World Applications</title>
        <introduction>
          <p>For the following exercises, use this scenario: A child enters a carousel that takes one minute to revolve once around. The child enters at the point <m>(0,1),</m> that is, on the due north position. Assume the carousel revolves counter clockwise.</p>
        </introduction>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-XYjCpDpywB-parts" original="PRECALC/modules/m49372/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>What are the coordinates of the child after 45 seconds?</li>
              <li>What are the coordinates of the child after 90 seconds?</li>
              <li>What is the coordinates of the child after 125 seconds?</li>
              <li>When will the child have coordinates <m>(0.707,–0.707)</m> if the ride lasts 6 minutes? (There are multiple answers.)</li>
              <li>When will the child have coordinates <m>(−0.866,−0.5)</m> if the ride last 6 minutes?</li>
            </ol>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>(0,-1)</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>37.5 seconds, 97.5 seconds, 157.5 seconds, 217.5 seconds, 277.5 seconds, 337.5 seconds</li>
              <li/>
            </ol>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
  
    <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-Ion0TMST2P" original="PRECALC/modules/m49398/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
      <title>Try It</title>
      <statement>
        <p>Solve exactly the following linear equation on the interval <m>[0,2π):2sinx+1=0.</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          <m>x=\frac{7π}{6},\frac{11π}{6}</m>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </exercise>
  
    <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-nZXr5h6aTu" original="PRECALC/modules/m49398/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
      <title>Try It</title>
      <statement>
        <p>Find all solutions for <m>tanx=\sqrt{3}.</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          <m>\frac{π}{3}±πk</m>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </exercise>
  
    <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-dk5ssgoTZB" original="PRECALC/modules/m49398/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
      <title>Try It</title>
      <statement>
        <p>Solve <m>cosθ=-0.2.</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          <m>θ≈1.7722±2πk</m> and <m>θ≈4.5110±2πk</m>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </exercise>
  
    <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-9OQ4ElhZ8L" original="PRECALC/modules/m49398/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
      <title>Try It</title>
      <statement>
        <p>Solve <m>sin^{2}θ=2cosθ+2,0 \le θ \le 2π.</m> [Hint: Make a substitution to express the equation only in terms of cosine.]</p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          <m>cosθ=-1,θ=π</m>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </exercise>
  
    <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-xFAtwVXxes" original="PRECALC/modules/m49398/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
      <title>Try It</title>
      <statement>
        <p>Solve the quadratic equation <m>2cos^{2}θ+cosθ=0.</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          <m>\frac{π}{2},\frac{2π}{3},\frac{4π}{3},\frac{3π}{2}</m>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </exercise>
  
    <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-ieCsla8MJC-parts" original="PRECALC/modules/m49398/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
        <statement>
          <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
            <li>Will there always be solutions to trigonometric function equations? If not, describe an equation that would not have a solution. Explain why or why not.</li>
            <li>When solving a trigonometric equation involving more than one trig function, do we always want to try to rewrite the equation so it is expressed in terms of one trigonometric function? Why or why not?</li>
            <li>When solving linear trig equations in terms of only sine or cosine, how do we know whether there will be solutions?</li>
          </ol>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
            <li>There will not always be solutions to trigonometric function equations. For a basic example, <m>cos(x)=−5.</m>
            </li>
            <li/>
            <li>If the sine or cosine function has a coefficient of one, isolate the term on one side of the equals sign. If the number it is set equal to has an absolute value less than or equal to one, the equation has solutions, otherwise it does not. If the sine or cosine does not have a coefficient equal to one, still isolate the term but then divide both sides of the equation by the leading coefficient. Then, if the number it is set equal to has an absolute value greater than one, the equation has no solution.</li>
          </ol>
        </solution>
      </exercise>
  
    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Algebraic</title>
        <introduction>
          <p>For the following exercises, find all solutions exactly on the interval <m>0 \le θ &lt; 2π.</m>
          </p>
        </introduction>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-GEtoY1UsKO-parts" original="PRECALC/modules/m49398/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>2sinθ=−\sqrt{2}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2sinθ=\sqrt{3}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2cosθ=1</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2cosθ=−\sqrt{2}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>tanθ=−1</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>tanx=1</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>cotx+1=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>4sin^{2}x-2=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>csc^{2}x-4=0</m>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{π}{3},\frac{2π}{3}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{3π}{4},\frac{5π}{4}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{π}{4},\frac{5π}{4}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{π}{4},\frac{3π}{4},\frac{5π}{4},\frac{7π}{4}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
            </ol>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
  
    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Algebraic</title>
        <introduction>
          <p>For the following exercises, solve exactly on <m>[0,2π).</m>
          </p>
        </introduction>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-3Cj8Ot7WMG-parts" original="PRECALC/modules/m49398/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>2cosθ=\sqrt{2}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2cosθ=−1</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2sinθ=−1</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2sinθ=−\sqrt{3}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2sin(3θ)=1</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2sin(2θ)=\sqrt{3}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2cos(3θ)=-\sqrt{2}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>cos(2θ)=-\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2sin(πθ)=1</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2cos(\frac{π}{5}θ)=\sqrt{3}</m>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>\frac{π}{4},\frac{7π}{4}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{7π}{6},\frac{11π}{6}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{π}{18}</m>, <m>\frac{5π}{18}</m>, <m>\frac{13π}{18}</m>, <m>\frac{17π}{18}</m>, <m>\frac{25π}{18}</m>, <m>\frac{29π}{18}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{3π}{12},\frac{5π}{12},\frac{11π}{12},\frac{13π}{12},\frac{19π}{12},\frac{21π}{12}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{1}{6},\frac{5}{6},\frac{13}{6},\frac{17}{6},\frac{25}{6},\frac{29}{6},\frac{37}{6}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
            </ol>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
  
    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Algebraic</title>
        <introduction>
          <p>For the following exercises, find all exact solutions on <m>[0,2π).</m>
          </p>
        </introduction>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-LxvvHqM8pQ-parts" original="PRECALC/modules/m49398/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>sec(x)sin(x)-2sin(x)=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>tan(x)-2sin(x)tan(x)=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2cos^{2}t+cos(t)=1</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2tan^{2}(t)=3sec(t)</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2sin(x)cos(x)-sin(x)+2cos(x)-1=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>cos^{2}θ=\frac{1}{2}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>sec^{2}x=1</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>tan^{2}(x)=-1+2tan(-x)</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>8sin^{2}(x)+6sin(x)+1=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>tan^{5}(x)=tan(x)</m>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>0,\frac{π}{3},π,\frac{5π}{3}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{π}{3},π,\frac{5π}{3}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{π}{3},\frac{3π}{2},\frac{5π}{3}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>0,π</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>π-sin^{-1}(-\frac{1}{4}),\frac{7π}{6},\frac{11π}{6},2π+sin^{-1}(-\frac{1}{4})</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
            </ol>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
  
    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Algebraic</title>
        <introduction>
          <p>For the following exercises, solve with the methods shown in this section exactly on the interval <m>[0,2π).</m>
          </p>
        </introduction>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-t6cDbdyLD4-parts" original="PRECALC/modules/m49398/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>sin(3x)cos(6x)-cos(3x)sin(6x)=−0.9</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>sin(6x)cos(11x)-cos(6x)sin(11x)=−0.1</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>cos(2x)cosx+sin(2x)sinx=1</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>6sin(2t)+9sint=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>9cos(2θ)=9cos^{2}θ-4</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>sin(2t)=cost</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>cos(2t)=sint</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>cos(6x)-cos(3x)=0</m>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>\frac{1}{3}(sin^{-1}(\frac{9}{10})),</m>
                <m>\frac{π}{3}-\frac{1}{3}(sin^{-1}(\frac{9}{10})),</m>
                <m>\frac{2π}{3}+\frac{1}{3}(sin^{-1}(\frac{9}{10})),</m>
                <m>π-\frac{1}{3}(sin^{-1}(\frac{9}{10})),</m>
                <m>\frac{4π}{3}+\frac{1}{3}(sin^{-1}(\frac{9}{10})),</m>
                <m>\frac{5π}{3}-\frac{1}{3}(sin^{-1}(\frac{9}{10}))</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>0</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>θ=sin^{-1}\left(\frac{2}{3}\right),</m>
                <m>π-sin^{-1}\left(\frac{2}{3}\right),</m>
                <m>π+sin^{-1}\left(\frac{2}{3}\right),</m>
                <m>2π-sin^{-1}\left(\frac{2}{3}\right)</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{3π}{2},\frac{π}{6},\frac{5π}{6}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
            </ol>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
  
    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Algebraic</title>
        <introduction>
          <p>For the following exercises, solve exactly on the interval <m>[0,2π).</m> Use the quadratic formula if the equations do not factor.</p>
        </introduction>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-iFoNGzZCko-parts" original="PRECALC/modules/m49398/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>tan^{2}x-\sqrt{3}tanx=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>sin^{2}x+sinx-2=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>sin^{2}x-2sinx-4=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>5cos^{2}x+3cosx-1=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>3cos^{2}x-2cosx-2=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>5sin^{2}x+2sinx-1=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>tan^{2}x+5tanx-1=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>cot^{2}x=-cotx</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>-tan^{2}x-tanx-2=0</m>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>0,\frac{π}{3},π,\frac{4π}{3}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>There are no solutions.</li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>cos^{-1}(\frac{1}{3}(1-\sqrt{7})),2π-cos^{-1}(\frac{1}{3}(1-\sqrt{7}))</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>tan^{-1}(\frac{1}{2}(\sqrt{29}-5)),π+tan^{-1}(\frac{1}{2}(-\sqrt{29}-5)),π+tan^{-1}(\frac{1}{2}(\sqrt{29}-5)),2π+tan^{-1}(\frac{1}{2}(-\sqrt{29}-5))</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>There are no solutions.</li>
            </ol>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
  
    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Algebraic</title>
        <introduction>
          <p>For the following exercises, find exact solutions on the interval <m>[0,2π).</m> Look for opportunities to use trigonometric identities.</p>
        </introduction>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-loFC6RfTSh-parts" original="PRECALC/modules/m49398/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>sin^{2}x-cos^{2}x-sinx=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>sin^{2}x+cos^{2}x=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>sin(2x)-sinx=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>cos(2x)-cosx=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{2tanx}{2-sec^{2}x}-sin^{2}x=cos^{2}x</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>1-cos(2x)=1+cos(2x)</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>sec^{2}x=7</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>10sinxcosx=6cosx</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>−3sint=15costsint</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>4cos^{2}x-4=15cosx</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>8sin^{2}x+6sinx+1=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>8cos^{2}θ=3-2cosθ</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>6cos^{2}x+7sinx-8=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>12sin^{2}t+cost-6=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>tanx=3sinx</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>cos^{3}t=cost</m>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li/>
              <li>There are no solutions.</li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>0,\frac{2π}{3},\frac{4π}{3}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{π}{4},\frac{3π}{4},\frac{5π}{4},\frac{7π}{4}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>sin^{-1}(\frac{3}{5}),\frac{π}{2},π-sin^{-1}(\frac{3}{5}),\frac{3π}{2}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>cos^{-1}(-\frac{1}{4})</m>, <m>2π-cos^{-1}(-\frac{1}{4})</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{π}{3},cos^{-1}(-\frac{3}{4}),2π-cos^{-1}(-\frac{3}{4}),\frac{5π}{3}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>cos^{-1}(\frac{3}{4}),cos^{-1}(-\frac{2}{3}),2π-cos^{-1}(-\frac{2}{3})</m>, <m>2π-cos^{-1}(\frac{3}{4})</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>0,\frac{π}{2},π,\frac{3π}{2}</m>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
  
    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Graphical</title>
        <introduction>
          <p>For the following exercises, algebraically determine all solutions of the trigonometric equation exactly, then verify the results by graphing the equation and finding the zeros. Use an interval of <m>[0,2π)</m>.</p>
        </introduction>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-HMU3cjsv2k-parts" original="PRECALC/modules/m49398/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>6sin^{2}x-5sinx+1=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>8cos^{2}x-2cosx-1=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>100tan^{2}x+20tanx-3=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2cos^{2}x-cosx+15=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>20sin^{2}x-27sinx+7=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>2tan^{2}x+7tanx+6=0</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>130tan^{2}x+69tanx-130=0</m>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>\frac{π}{3},cos^{−1}(-\frac{1}{4}),2π-cos^{−1}(-\frac{1}{4}),\frac{5π}{3}</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
              <li>There are no solutions.</li>
              <li/>
              <li>
                <m>π+tan^{−1}(−2)</m>, <m>π+tan^{−1}(-\frac{3}{2}),</m>
                <m>2π+tan^{−1}(−2),</m>
                <m>2π+tan^{−1}(-\frac{3}{2})</m>
              </li>
              <li/>
            </ol>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
  
    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Technology</title>
