            <caption>A triangle inside a triangle. The outer triangle is formed by vertices A, B, and D. Side B D is the base. The inner triangle shares vertices A and B. The last vertex C is located on the base side of the outer triangle between vertices B and D. Angle B is 60 degrees, side A D is 10, and side A C is 9.</caption>
            <image source="PRECALC/CNX_Precalc_Figure_08_01_223.jpg" width="80%"/>
          </figure>
        </statement>
      </exercise>
  
